content.description: Begin on the right side of the face by making an easy step up onto a big ledge then ascend up and left up the smears and crimps.
content.protection: One bolt, trees and a big root. Using the root requires little extension while a tree requires ~20 webbing loop. All routes on this wall share the same anchor setup.

content.description: Begin climbing below the bulge (same start as Bulge) and traverse up and left, around it, until you've bypassed it. Traverse right and continue upward.
content.protection: One bolt, trees and a big root. Using the root requires little extension while a tree requires ~20 webbing loop. All routes on this wall share the same anchor setup.

content.description: Climb the arete left of the routes. Tops out just left of its neighbors to finish at the same anchors.
content.protection: Anchor from trees, massive roots or the bolt but redirect off the rightmost branch of the madrona directly above the arete. Takes pro to 1".

content.description:
Route begins below the roof on the right. Begin on dirty holds before traversing left around the roof, then back right to dodge the next and finally top out.

Needs more cleaning.
content.protection: Bring plenty of webbing to extend from the trees above the route. Given the loose rock at the top, helmets are a good idea as well.

content.description: Begin below and pass the bulge.
content.protection: One bolt, trees and a big root. Using the root requires little extension while a tree requires ~20 webbing loop. All routes on this wall share the same anchor setup.
